# No tool branding

Do not add branding or attribution for Cursor, Copilot, Claude, ChatGPT, or any other AI tool in:

- Git commit messages
- Pull request titles or bodies
- GitHub issue comments
- User-facing documentation (`README.md`, release notes, changelogs)

The user handles attribution separately when they choose.

## Forbidden patterns

- "Made with Cursor" or links to cursor.com
- "Generated by …", "Co-authored-by: …" for AI tools (unless the user explicitly requests it)
- Tool logos, badges, or footer lines in PR templates

## Allowed

- Technical content only: what changed, why, test plan, `Closes #N`
- Internal agent docs (`AGENTS.md`, `.cursor/skills/`) may reference workflow paths; no product marketing

## Commits and PRs

Write as a human contributor: imperative mood, no meta-commentary about how the code was produced.
